The paper deals with the performance analysis of multi-cell multi-user massive MIMO downlink systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), communication (cs.COMM), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper discusses the impact of imperfect channel state information, pilot contamination, and channel spatial correlation on the performance of the system, which are all relevant topics in these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.NI, and cs.SI, followed by cs.COMM and cs.MA.
